{
  "text": "Based on the results from the Society of Thoracic Surgeons Adult Cardiac Surgery National Database, Brennan et al [CITATION_1] reported that overall risk of death and embolism was small in the first 3 months following bioprosthetic AVR. Despite the lower risk of such events in patients on aspirin and warfarin compared to aspirin alone, this strategy was associated with an increased risk of bleeding.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "12476088"
